Something I never paid attention to….

RECOVERY ❤️‍🩹.

Most of my life has been focused around sports. Giving everything I had on the field when playing lacrosse and speeding through tennis drills on the court. 
Rinse and repeat. 
There was no talk of cold plunging, hot plunge or sauna. I never heard of a foam roller or anything to help with muscle soreness. You just sucked it up and moved onto your next practice or game. 

When I joined the Team at Anatomy 2 years ago, I kept hearing of people using the sanctuary. I paid very little attention to it. My thought was- who has time for that? Honest truth, I didn’t see the sanctuary until 6 months after working there. 🤦🏻‍♀️ 

The answer to that question is: people who want to take care of their body, mind and spirit. I didn’t realize this then. I was so hyper focused on getting things done that I didn’t focus on what my go go go lifestyle, little sleep, and stress was doing to my body. 

I won’t say that I cold plunge and do everything I should on a daily basis because that would be a lie. Work, life, and choosing to workout over plunge sometimes get in the way. 
When I think about what I want to do most in 2023 for myself, it’s take better care of my health both physically and mentally. 

I’m on my feet for most of the day and lately I’ve been dealing with some lateral foot pain. Instead of pushing through it I’m seeing the PT at Anatomy and using this foot massager by @renphogroup .
I also use their massage gun after days with heavy lifts. This is all a part of my recovery process that I will be taking into 2023.

When you recover well, your body will respond even better. This was something that took me a long time to figure out an appreciate. Don’t wait on this like I did, take better care of yourself. Your body will thank you!

Core Inferno 🔥

There’s many benefits to a strong core besides getting shredded abs. 
To list a few:
✨Reduce Back Pain
✨Injury Prevention
✨Improved Lifting Mechanics
✨Balance
✨Stability
✨Improve Athletic Performance
✨Helps Posture

Give these 3 movements a try.

1️⃣ Knees bent at 90 degrees and hold db up. Complete 15-20 reps on the right then 15-20 on the left. 

2️⃣Turn toes inwards and make the tip of a triangle with your legs 🔼. 20 reps. 

3️⃣Coil up and move as slow as a snail 🐌. Knees come as close to shoulders as possible. 10 slow reps is all you should need if you’re doing it right. This will feel SPICY 🌶️. 

⚡️Complete 3-4 rounds!!

22 years ago on January 18, 2001, I went through a family tragedy that left me broken. My life has never been the same since but with time you grow through the pain.

Most of you know me as the energizer bunny coaching class with a smile and keeping the vibes high. That 💯 is me but that doesn’t mean I don’t have my moments. I struggle too. You see, we’re all going through something.

This post isn’t for sympathy, it’s for transparency. Through sharing, we learn more about people and hopefully come to understand that everyone goes through tough times. You’re not alone!! It’s always been important to me to be real on this platform. So while a lot of what I do on here looks like a fun time, sometimes my workouts are therapy to heal what’s been broken. I find strength in pushing through barriers. Discipline has got me to where I am. Not just discipline in the gym, but being disciplined with my dedication to healing. 
Thank you to everyone that’s given such positive energy today in class and to the people who know it’s tough and have reached out. 🤍

Why train obliques❓❓

👊🏼Helps prevent injuries
👊🏼Aids in rotating
👊🏼Aids in bending your torso.

10 one direction 10 the other. Slow and controlled. 

💥KNEELING BANDED ROTATION:
10-15 Reps Each Side

💥PALOFF PRESS W/ LATERAL FLEXION:
Probably one of the hardest. Anti rotation and resist lateral movement of the hips. Try 10 slow reps. 

💥SIDE PLANK HIP DIP/KNEE TUCK:
Also challenging. Try 8-10 reps here.

💥SINGLE LEG SEATED RUNNER:
10 each leg

💥SEATED RUNNER:
Here’s another version with both feet in band. Little bit easier but still challenging. Go for 20 reps. 

💥SEATED BANDED KNEE TUCKS:
Tuck in knees side to side. 20 reps.

What You Need:
🧅 Onion
🍋 Lemon
🍯 Honey

Onion, lemon, honey, and salt are commonly used ingredients in natural remedies for cough relief. Here's how each component may contribute to soothing a cough:

1. 🧅 : Onions contain compounds like flavonoids and sulfur compounds that have antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. These properties may help reduce inflammation and irritation in the respiratory system, providing relief from cough symptoms.

2. 🍋 : Lemons are rich in vitamin C, which supports the immune system and can help fight off infections. Additionally, lemon juice's acidic nature may help break up mucus and phlegm, making it easier to expel.

3. 🍯 : Honey has long been used as a natural cough suppressant. It has soothing properties that can help alleviate throat irritation and coughing. Honey also has antimicrobial properties that may help fight off bacteria or viruses causing the cough.

4. 🧂 : Saltwater gargles can help reduce throat inflammation and irritation. When mixed with warm water, salt can help soothe the throat, reduce mucus, and provide temporary relief from coughing.

To use these ingredients together for cough relief, you can try the following recipe:

1. Finely chop or grate half an onion.
2. Squeeze the juice of half a lemon into a bowl.
3. Add a tablespoon of honey and a pinch of salt to the bowl.
4. Mix all the ingredients together until well combined.
5. Let it sit out for a few minutes before placing it in the refrigerator. Take a shot or tablespoon of the mixture as needed, several times a day.

Athens it’s been real!! 

Athens, Greece is the capital city and the historical and cultural heart of the country. 🇬🇷🏛️ Known for its rich history and ancient landmarks, Athens is a must-visit destination for history buffs and architecture enthusiasts. The most famous landmark is the Parthenon, a magnificent temple atop the Acropolis hill dedicated to the goddess Athena. 🏛️🌟 This was breathtaking and a must! 
The Acropolis Museum, located nearby, houses an impressive collection of ancient Greek artifacts. 

The city also offers a vibrant modern side, with bustling markets, trendy neighborhoods, and a thriving food scene. 🐙 🍽️🛍️ The Plaka district is a popular area for tourists, with its charming narrow streets, traditional tavernas, and souvenir shops. This evil eye 🧿 jacket was bought in Plaka. Hand painted by an Athenian artist 👩‍🎨.
Monastiraki Square is another bustling area, known for its flea market and vibrant atmosphere. The 360 cocktail bar offers magnificent views. 

Athens is also home to several other notable attractions, such as the Temple of Olympian Zeus, the Ancient Agora, and the National Archaeological Museum. Additionally, the city boasts beautiful parks, including the National Garden, where visitors can relax and enjoy a peaceful escape. Definitely walk by the changing of the guards on your way. 

With a mix of ancient history, modern charm, and warm Greek hospitality, Athens is a city that offers a diverse and unforgettable experience. I recommend going for about 3 days then head to the islands. ☀️

Sometimes you have to remind yourself of what you’ve done to recognize what you’re capable of. 

Being quite honest, I felt life slipping when I lost my best friend in June. The word PURPOSE kept sticking out in my mind and trying to find meaning in what my purpose was —- well that was challenging. 

I decided I needed to take action and lean into things that challenge me. 
I started with deciding to bike 1.5 million meters/932 miles which is almost from Florida to my home state of Rhode Island to put things in perspective. The goal was to raise awareness during breast cancer awareness month in October. It took waking up early mornings, saddle sores from being on there for hours, and more water than I’ve ever consumed in my entire life lol. I had tunnel vision and all I could see was the finish line and my best friend cheering me on. 

After that goal was complete I followed through on my goal of completing and passing real estate school within one week. I didn’t want to miss coaching for weeks on end so I did what I thought was simply insane and registered for the week course🥵. Many might not know this but I have a reading comprehension disorder that was discovered when I was young. This means I had to work extra hard to read and understand material that looked completely foreign to me. I’m given extra time on tests but I wanted to prove to myself that I could defy the odds stacked against me and pass without using the extra time. A lot of affirmations each day and reminding myself that my reading disorder doesn’t define me or take away from how smart I am. 🧠
I cried when my test scan went through and I passed. Tears of joy and a proud moment for myself that I truly needed after the last few months of life just throwing daggers at me. 🗡️ 

The purpose of sharing is to help remind you that you can achieve hard things and when you lose sight of that - remind yourself of what you’ve OVERCOME or ACHIEVED. 

The sun will always shine again. It may feel different but it’s there and waiting for you to lean in and feel it. ☀️ 

Ok back to studying. I still have a state exam to pass 💪🏼🧠⚡️

Love you guys. Thank you for all the support! 🙌🏻❤️GRATEFUL
